com.solvvy.cluster

Class ClusteredFeatureVector<T extends Scoreable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.solvvy.cluster.ClusteredFeatureVector<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the clustered element.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Scoreable<ClusteredFeatureVector<T>>, Comparable<Scoreable<ClusteredFeatureVector<T>>>

    public class ClusteredFeatureVector<T extends Scoreable<T>>
extends Object
implements Scoreable<ClusteredFeatureVector<T>>
    A ClusteredFeatureVector is a clustered Scoreable element, its feature vector, and its distance from the centroid of its cluster. ClusteredFeatureVector implements Scoreable by delegating all method calls to its element.
